<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="neither-pron">neither <strong><em>pron</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'naɪðə(r),'niːðə(r)/    美 /'naɪðər,'niːðər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(两者之中) 无一个：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Now neither of my parents give me money. 
现在，父母都不给我钱了。</p><footer>北师大④ – 11</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Neither of them</strong> has / have a car. 
他们两个都没车。</p></div>

<p>注: “neither of + 复数名词 / 代词”作主语时，谓语动词既可以用单数，也可以用复数。  </p>
<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>The research group produced two reports based on the survey, but <strong><em>_</em></strong> contained any useful suggestions.  （2015 福建改）  </li>
<li>She’d lived in London and Manchester, but she liked <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ and moved to Cambridge.   （2014 四川改）  </li>
<li>Larry asks Bill and Peter to go on a picnic with him, but <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ of them wants to, because they have work to do.   （2012 全国改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. neither  2. neither  3. neither   </p></div>